          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A cylindrical pellet was formed from commercially",
                "available natural cerium dioxide powder CeO2 99.9%",
                "The tablet was weighed on an analytical scale and its",
                "thickness measured with a precision of 0.001 mm to",
                "determine the material density for stopping power",
                "calculations as well as the amount of target atoms.",
                "The dimensions of a typical pellet were: diameter 13 mm",
                "height 6.4 mm, weight 3.9 g.  The pellet was glued",
                "onto an aluminum block and the surface precut on the",
                "rotation microtome for precise adjustment after",
                "irradiation.  The holder was finally placed into a",
                "helium-cooled aluminum target body.",
                "One hour after the end of bombardment, the aluminum",
                "block with the pellet was removed from the target",
                "holder and mounted into the microtome.",
                "The pellet was cut into thin slices of 4 mum each.",
                "10 slices of 4 mum each were combined, equaling a",
                "sample of 40 mum thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "- By author - abstract:",
                "the cross-section measurement of particle-induced",
                "nuclear reactions is commonly performed using the",
                "stacked foil method. If the target material is fragile",
                "or sensitive to air or moisture, this technique is",
                "hardly practical.  This communication describes a new",
                "method for the simple, reliable and precise",
                "determination of cross-sections.  A pressed pellet of a",
                "stable compound of the desired element is irradiated",
                "and then cut into thin slices with a microtome.  The",
                "radionuclides in each slice are measured and the",
                "cross-sections for the nuclear reactions involved are",
                "derived by standard equations.  The feasibility of the",
                "pellet method was demonstrated by measuring the",
                "excitation functions of the 140Ce(p,2n)139 Pr and",
                "140Ce(p,3n)138-m-Pr reactions.  The calculated results",
                "were in good agreement with the experimental yield",
                "obtained from thick target irradiations."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-T",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The total errors in the measured cross-sections",
                "were estimated by taking square roots of the sums of",
                "the squares of the individual errors"
              ]
